author: News Tribune
title: Cross Country: Jefferson City, Helias run in Borgia Invitational
text:
Share 
WASHINGTON, Mo. — The Jefferson City and Helias cross country teams competed Saturday at the St. Francis Borgia Invitational. 
Helias finished fifth in the boys race and second in the girls, and the Jays were seventh and fourth, respectively. The Jefferson City boys team’s top seven runners did not compete, nor did the girls team’s top five. 
Elliot Knernschield finished fourth for Helias in the boys race, and Kayla Yanskey led the girls, finishing fourth as well. 
Jefferson City took sixth in the JV boys race, and Helias finished seventh. The Jays were paced by Brady Stockman’s 28th-place finish, and Riley Scott was the top Crusaders finisher at 26th. 
In the JV girls race, Helias took first, and the Lady Jays finished third. Helias had six runners in the top 10: Katherine McDonald (third), Rachel Smith (fifth), Maddie Casten (seventh), Elly Bowles (eighth), Taylor Koelling (ninth) and Katerina Careaga (10th). The Lady Jays were led by Lauren Tuck, who finished fourth. VARSITY BOYS
